caption: Great dinner to go options

Delicious very authentic Persian style fine dining cuisine. Bold middle eastern flavors with all the traditional sides. Service is well trained and friendly. They help guide any newcomers through the Persian experience.
I miss dining there! Their pastas are probably one of the best in town, and they go perfectly well with their quality wine selection. Their takeouts did not disappoint me!
Save your money, they discriminate....
Great Valentine’s Day dinner, can’t wait to dine in person whenever the world returns to normal.
Never a bad meal at The Red Hen. Amazing service, adorable decor and top-quality food

This place is truly fantastic. Not cheap, but worth every penny and more. The magic is in the details. It takes something special to make a simple pasta dish that is comforting, refreshing, subtle, and memorable, and Red Hen hits the nail on the head. Additionally, the cocktail program is top-notch, easily goes toe to toe with local cocktail joints like Truxton Inn, Service Bar, or even The Gibson (almost). The location is built out beautifully, but is still inviting and unpretentious. I only make it there for special occasions, but they never disappoint.

My friend put in a pick up order for us. We were traveling and found this restaurant.It was awful. Some of the worst food I’ve had in awhile. I had Rigatoni and was very disappointed at the portion as well as bland flavor. I also ordered spaghetti squash . Terrible. . It’s been a little while since that experience but Suffice it to say we never ate there again. There are better places.

Had the rigatoni and it was DELICIOUS! We ordered takeout and I was a little surprise by the size of the box, it looked like a leftover cardboard small box lol for $25 I thought it was a bit much but still really yummy!
Gourmet in a beautiful space.
Not really that good
The scallops were hand picked by Nancy herself and flown in from Maine. You could taste Nancy's love in every bite. I visited PRE-COVID and it was jam packed on a Tuesday night.

5-star experience every single time I've dined or ordered take out here. I am absolutely in love with their pasta. There are a lot of Italian spots around the DMV but this is my #1 choice for sure. Thank you!

The portion sizes of our carryout order were absurdly small. I certainly wasn’t expecting a gallon of pasta as if we were at the Olive Garden, but I’m astonished at the audacity of charging someone $19 for half a small container’s worth of cacio e pepe. Or $10 for a tiny container of tiramisu. After spending over $80 for tonight’s celebratory dinner, my boyfriend and I still had to make more food at home because the two pastas we got were only barely enough food for him, let alone both of us, which is saying something since we tend to eat small portions anyway. I can’t fault them for the taste of the food, the two bites in the box were good. But to be honest, we have had comparable food but at a much better value from other Italian focused restaurants in the city. I would not return, but if price isn’t a factor for you then definitely check it out.
Very rude people run this restaurant. I would never go here again
Ignore the troll scum below and their fake/made up reviews.  I’ve been here on three separate occasions and it was excellent each time.
Nothing Special.  Food tastes like rubber. They are not the most friendly bunch :(
Delicious. We had the fregola salad, meatballs, arancini balls, gnocchi, squid ink pasta, and the halibut, and everything was great.
Very expensive and rude people.
One of the best restaurants I've ever been to.
Worst food I have ever eaten...The food was cold, uncooked, nasty
Amazing food!! The panna cotta is heavenly! Super fast pickup and friendly too :)

It is not clear that you must order online. Also people are taking a chance coming out to eat trusting that your staff is clean. so dont treat them like they are bothering you even when they have on a mask.the only other reason i can think of is they treat black people different...
Bad staff, make it more about politics instead of the food
Thanks for the safe pickup and delicious pasta and main course fish. Presentation even in the little to-go boxes was beautiful. Perfectly cooked pasta with flavorful, deeply rich sauces.
Favorite restaurant in DC. The dishes and wine never disappoint. The open room gives the place a nice atmosphere. Try the pasta dish and share one of the large dishes if you have enough appetite.
Amazing local cuisine
They like to play politics instead of running a business. Food sucks as well as service

Delicious Italian fare in a rustically cozy setting. The vibe is convivial, staff is great, good is exquisite. Favorites include the rigatoni, squid ink pasta, and the cracked pepper macaroni and cheese.
Food was cold, service was very cold also.
Food was not memorable. Staff was unfortunately memorable with bad and inconsiderate service. Also a bit expensive. Don't waste your time or money.
(Translated by Google) Very good prices  (Original) Muy buenos precios

We did take out and our order was ready at the time it was specified. Finding a parking spot here might be difficult. Coming to the food, we got the mezzi rigatoni, wild mushroom mafalde and the squid ink linguini all three were delicious. But the rigatoni was amazing and it’s a must try item on the menu. Just a head up, the portions are a bit small for the price. One dish might not fill your stomach. But the overall quality and taste was great.

I just called today (Saturday at 5:30pm May 9th, 2020) to order food for 5 adults because the toast app was not responding & the service I received over the phone was horrible. Even though their current policy is to only accept orders via phone for ppl with food allergies, I figured bc the app was unresponsive, they would consider taking my order over the phone. Instead, I was met with attitude. When I told them that I attempted to use the app but it was unresponsive, the person on the end said my internet connection must not have been strong enough to complete the order, which is both untrue and unacceptable. I was denied the opportunity to place an order. I’m a frequent customer at Red Hen and typically have positive experiences there, but today the staff was rude and very difficult to deal with. I’M NEVER GOING BACK TO THIS PLACE. During this pandemic, I wanted to do my part to support the restaurants we love and other local businesses, and can’t believe that I was essentially turned away.

The food was great but the wait was incredibly long and the service was off.  The seafood linguini and the chicken liver mousse was on point. My partner’s spaghetti squash appetizer was also good.  The servers walked by our table several times and kind of ignored us, didn’t ask if we wanted another drink or dessert (which we did).  Not sure I’d come back anytime soon but am glad I gave it a try.

For the high prices I was expecting much more. The food was nothing special and the serving was small. I won't be back. Response to the owner: I didn't say when I ate at your restaurant. It sounds as if you are questioning my honesty. Check your attitude, accept the criticism, learn, and move on.
My first time to this place was 2 years ago and I’ve been In love ever since !
Great food! Pricey as DC is.

I’m sorry to say my experience was disappointing. The cocktail was underwhelming.  The texture of the past was all wrong, without that “chew” that properly cooked fresh pasta has. The sauce wasn’t anything special.  Given that it’s a super hyped restaurant, it is probably worth a visit. Who knows? Maybe I was there on a bad night?

By far one of if not my favorite restaurant in DC. Making a reservation is highly recommended just because sometimes there's quite a wait (although sometimes you can get lucky with a seat at the bar!). I prefer their summer menu to their winter one, but you can't go wrong either way.
Dirty restaurant. Horrible staff. Wont go again.

I’m torn between a 3 and 4 star review, since I felt that the food was pretty good but didn’t think this restaurant was as good as people around here make it out to be. And the service was a bit odd.  I snagged a reservation by chance. We decided to start with some drinks. I got the Suit and Tie and my boyfriend got another drink with coffee in it. My drink was basically all alcohol with little to no other flavor in it, which was...interesting. I didn’t even finish it.  We ordered the chicken liver mousse toast which was actually quite good. The spaghetti squash appetizer was also pretty tasty.  For our meals, we ordered the cacio y pepe and the seafood linguini. The cacio was solid and the seafood linguini was also tasty.  For dessert, we ordered the chocolate cake and subbed out the mint gelato for the cherry gelato. Easily the best part of the meal.  The reason I’m docking some stars off is because 1) I felt this place was overpriced for food that was good but not amazing and 2) our server seemed super passive aggressive and there was something totally off-putting about the way they spoke to us. Here’s an example: When the server offered to take away our small plates after the squash, I tried to help and put my silverware on top of the plate. They then took my plate, looked extremely upset, sat it BACK down, rearranged the silverware and picked it back up.  Our server didn’t have any suggestions on the menu either, which was odd because we were clearly not sure what to order from the antipasti section. They walked by our table a bunch and didn’t ask how the meal was going. Just seemed like they really wanted to rush us out of there.  Not sure I’d come back anytime soon but am glad I gave it a try.

Trying to get in here without a booking is a waste of time. They say that you can walk in but after trying to do just that two nights in a row, I think it is safe to say that's not true. Even if you arrive, as suggested on their website, before 7 or after 9.

We used to love it here because it was super family friendly. The food was always good. Today we went and it was absolutely disgusting. The lettuce was whittled. The peppers in the quesadilla where raw. Even the brownie was dry and tasted like nothing. Extremely disappointed. Idk what changed but something did.

Went to DC for a conference and happen to fall upon this place for dinner. All of the food options were great. perfectly chose a cocktail to go with the food I had ordered as my entree. Desserts were also incredible.
This is a wonderful place to eat.  My daughter treated me to dinner here when I visited.
So delicious!
Amazing pasta and good portions at a friendly price.
Great food, highly recommend.
Neat Place. Great food and service

Lovely location in Bloomingdale. Service is always phenomenal, and the food is even better. I highly recommend the squid ink pasta. It can become loud in there, but overall, it is a cozy, intimate setting.
Excellent rigatoni. Chicken liver mouse. Try the orange wine
Great food and great atmosphere!  Try the short rib!
Great food and great service.
Recommended by Chef #CarlosGonzalez Gallitos Salsa

The food was divine. I will have memories of that hazelnut custard for a lifetime. The fried brussel sprouts set the tone and the service was just excellent throughout. One of the best restaurant experiences my life.
Good food. Brings new taste to the table. Good wine options. Service is good too. And it’s great value for what you pay.
Delicious food, drinks, and dessert. Staff are so friendly. Just make sure you make reservations for ahead of time if you're thinking of coming here!
Pretty delicious. A little pricey for the portions, but all in all a very pleasant experience.
So delicious, simple and good. Every time I come, I'm newly impressed.
Absolutely Fantastic!  Service, food, and wine or drinks!  5 stars without a doubt!
Love everything about this plce!
Amazing food!
One of DC's best restaurants

Menu listing are terrible, all servings offered on the menu are very minimal and have a focal point on specific individuals. Overpriced, unappetizing = not worth it. Don’t waste your money here; go to McDonalds. Although the atmosphere indoors is great.
Just. So. Good.

(Translated by Google) The place is very good, the service is very good and the menu, despite not being very extensive or varied, is also very good. It is not my favorite place in the area, but it is worth visiting. At least to have a drink at the bar. If you want to eat, it is highly recommended to make a reservation.  (Original) El local está muy bien, el servicio es muy bueno y la carta, pese a no ser muy extensa o variada, está también muy bien. No es mi sitio favorito de la zona, pero sí merece la pena visitarlo. Al menos para tomar algo en la barra. Si se quiere comer, es muy recomendable hacer una reserva.

I'm pretty hard on DC-area restaurants, which in general I find over-priced and under-performing.  Red Hen was my daughter's pick - and I expected it to be like so many others.   Imagine her surprise when at the end of the meal I turned to her and said "This was excellent on all accounts  - we will come back".   It's all done right here - from the quality of the meal to the service to the casual/upscale ambiance.   Prices are reasonable compared to other trendy eateries.  Everything was right on the mark and the whole family truly enjoyed our dining experience.
(Translated by Google) Amuse bouche.  (Original) Amuse bouche.

The service was phenomonal, and tbe food was fantastic. Not only was the flavor amazing, but the presentation and texture combined into a perfect combination. All of the dishes were originals, so it was difficult to decide. We had three courses. They changed the silver with each course. I was very impressed.
Red Hen is always a great experience. Amazing unpretentious food/wine menu. Fresh in house made pasta everyday. I love the ambiance and think it's a great spot for a date :)
one of my favorite truly neighborhood restaurants in dc. friendly, super knowledgeable service, delicious pastas, and chicken liver pate.
Solidly good, but I wish they changed the menu a bit more.
Food was amazing. Our server Collette provided great recommendations.
Amazing pasta spot with great wines, sides and friendly staff.
Good service, bomb food. The homemade pasta is especially delicious. Highly recommend the carrot cake for dessert.

Pretty good cocktails and whiskey selection, though not mind blowing. Service was friendly and good, I liked the vibe of the place - very neighborhoods. The pickle chips are absolutely fantastic. I would probably go back.

Possibly the best mean I have ever eaten in my life. We ordered a lot of dishes and the sharied everything family style. Each one was better than the one before. Great selection of wines. The service was impeccable. This has become my go to restaurant in DC.

The staff here is incredible. Our waitress helped us choose the top dishes and our wine pairing, and we were not disappointed. Highly recommend the cavatelli and rigatoni. The real winner here, however, was the Salted Butterscotch "Budino" which is quite possibly the best dessert I've ever had.
Best spot to eat in DC. Hands down.
Consistently excellent
Pricy, issues with service, but food was soooo good!
The chicken liver mousse is outstanding! Rigatoni with fennel ragu is a must.
Everything was really well balanced with great flavors over 2 visits here.
Delicious food and excellent service!
Always top notch dining!!! Delicious food.
Good fine dining restaurant

One of the best meals I've had in the District. Waiter was attentive and seemed to speak knowledgeably about the food and drink recommendations. All food was cooked perfectly and tasted great. If it were easier to get a table at a reasonable time, I'd go more often. However, I recommend visiting if you have the chance.
Great food, great service.

The Red Hen is easily my first thought when someone comes into town and wants amazing Italian food with service to match. The wait can be long - sometimes up to two hours - but try walking in and grabbing a spot at the bar even if you don't have a reservation. Their burrata is served differently each season and is a must order. All of their pastas are a delight, especially the Mezze Rigatoni. Dishes are between $15- $30 and all are substantial portions for the price.
Best meal in a long time, food very well prepared and presented
Best Italian neighborhood spot. All the dishes are a good portion and exquisite. Chicken liver mousse for life. Well priced wine list and wonderfully curated. The service has always been impeccable.
Fantastic food
Great food and excellent service! Homeade pasta was like mom's and the chicken liver mousse was heavenly! I closed my eyes and savored every bite.
Very cool atmosphere and nice service. Busy though so get reservations.
Superb cuisine! Should have a Michelin star, shocking it does not. Trendy, but not pretentious atmosphere. Great and knowledgeable servers. Wish it was easier to get a reservation.
Wait is insane and, food is good not great.
Great food and atmosphere. Amazing wine list.

Overall great dinner.  Appetizers were a bit underwhelming, but cocktails were great.  The pasta is amazing and highly recommended.  The general pacing of the meal felt hurried and we were served mains when appetizers were still on the table even with waiting to order until once the appetizers were served.  The wine list is great and relatively affordable.  Server was very nice and helpful.  I did not like being sat so close to the kitchen's heatlamps but asking to move would have been difficult as they're very busy on Saturday nights.  Go and get the fresh made pasta!
Great food, not pretentious, gem of a place

Horrible front of the house.  We saw reviews with similar complaints but decided to try it anyways.  I literally heard the hostess turn away 2 elderly woman & then comment "we wouldn't do that to xxx (waiters name)".  My husband and I walked out on principle.

Kinda expensive for no reason. Although the food tasted great, the portion size sucks. At least the staff were super cool, but I wouldn't come back here again. There's probably a better Italian food restaurant out there.
Amazing experience.  It was a bit of a wait, but totally worth it.  I suggest making reservations and try the cauliflower, it's is amazing!

Friday night in DC.  We had not made reservations for dinner and decided to "wing it".  We were recommended to go to the Red Hen by the bar tender at The Gibson.  We were welcomed with open arms and despite them being very busy, they found a spot for us.  This restaurant is great.  It is full of locals.  A great atmosphere....and despite being busy it was not so noisy and the service was superb.  The food was good, honest, tasty food.  The wine was excellent.  We loved it and would happily make it our local (if we lived in DC!).  Thank you to Robyn and Amy and all the staff
Absolutely best experience ever. The food is top notch and the staff is so knowledgeable and friendly! Can't wait to go back!
Great vibe, excellent service, creative and tasty dishes. Get the brownie for dessert!
Food was pretty ok, although pricy for what it was.
One of the best meals in DC. Pastas are amazing. Cauliflower is so great. Staff is knowledgeable. Neighborhood vibe.
as good as they say in the reviews!  Also expect long waits (or wish for a cancellation) and "animated" noise levels inside their wonderfully rustic building.

Phenomenal. Everyone should go here. I had the burrata, which was incredible. Light and airy but velvety smooth. The mafalde verde lamb ragu for my dinner was sublime. Perfectly al dente with an expertly crafted sauce.

Lovely tratorria with great service and wine list. Highly recommend the whipped ricotta on toast that is drizzled with honey as a starter. We also really enjoy the burrata appetizer and anything else seasonal on the menu. As for the pasta, the rigatoni and (off menu) cacio e pepe are absolutely delicious...the latter rivals, and on a really good night, outdoes the best cacio e pepe I've had in Rome.  Short ribs and scallops are highlights of the entree menu. My husband is a big fan of the maple custard dessert topped with crushed hazelnuts...you pretty much can't go wrong with anything on the menu.

Great Italian spot. Make sure to try to get a reservation. An 8pm reservation for Saturday night took about 3 weeks in advance. They have a great little organic garden outside designed by Love & Carrots, try to get a table facing it.  If you want to try your luck without a reservation, you can try to grab a seat at the bar which can also get crowded.
Lovely ambiance
Can't beat this place in the neighborhood. Great staff and food.
Good pasta, but prices have crept up substantially over the last year. Mains are fine, but nothing too out of the ordinary.

Finally got to try this magical place for a birthday celebration with a few friends. We had an exceptionally good evening, which started with one of the most passionate and attentive waiters I have ever had in my life. The many cocktails, appetizers, entrees and desserts which we tried were all fantastic. I can't wait to go back.
famazing!!!  Rigatoni, cauliflower, risotto balls, soooooo good!
Consistency is a hallmark of a fine dining experience, and Red Hen acheives this effortlessly. The seasonal menu ensures new surprises will never fail to delight.
Food was really great.  Waiter was enthusiastic and knowledgeable of the menu and the wine selections.  The only downside was that it was a little expensive for the quality.
BEST ITALIAN! Great atmosphere all the food was divine! Definitely coming back oh and definitely order the pasta! Mangia Mangia!
Wow, this brought me back to Italy.
Dope ass pasta

I can't recommend this place highly enough. Amazing food and our server Ejeon had great drink suggestions after discussing our tastes. The Rittenhouse Black Manhattan was perfect. Week night, two people, we walked in around 6 and were seated right away. The burrata was ok, but the cauliflower appetizer is a must try! We also had a Ricotta Crostini that I really liked.  The Short Rib was one of the best things I've ever eaten, and the Rigatoni was al dente like I can never pull off at home. All that said, if you only eat one thing here, be sure it's the Maple Custard. It's just insanely good! 5 Stars without hesitation. I'll definitely be back.
Good food, bad acoustics.
Solid option for that neighborhood.
Delicious food, but small entries.
The staff was above and beyond. The food was fantastic and they have a great wine selection as well.

One of my go-to places in DC.  The food and service are always great.  The only downside is that it is always really loud in the restaurant, and it can be hard to hear the person sitting across from you.
Amazing all around. Can't wait to get back.

This is by far and away one of the best restaurants in DC. The menu is seasonal and always has unique, fresh dishes that really highlight the quality of the ingredient. The prices are very fair, and it's a place that you could go and eat a good meal for 2 for under $100 on a night date night or something. The staff are very friendly and knowledgeable about their menu and wines. I live down the street and sometimes will pop in on a weekday to just get one of their pastas.  The rigatoni, as is known, is the best dish. And the chicken liver fig spread. And trout roulettes. Amazing all around.

Fantastic food, even better service.  One of the drinks I had was the best of that type I'd ever had -- so the bar knows what it's doing.  The drawbacks?  The place is tiny -- good luck getting a table!  The decor?  What's up with that firewood/rustic motif?  If you can get in there, I highly recommend it.

It was a nice small vibe.  Pasta was very reasonably priced and tasted great.  Craft beer selection was ok but not great.  The other couple we were with said the service is usually excellent but the waiter we had was good but he didn't do anything an average waiter doesn't do.   Overall it was really good experience but for all the talk it gets I did expect a little more.  Maybe my next trip will get it bumped up to a 5 stars.
Excellent meal here with friends. Really some of the best pasta I have ever eaten. Small plates and appetizers were very good. Excellent cocktails and interesting wine list.
Good food but way, WAY overpriced for what you get. Atmospere is noisy though it's very quaint in decor and staff is excellent!
so good

Hands down the best pasta I've had outside of Italy. The sausage fennel pasta is amazing. The apps/entrees rotate but there are also a few items that permanently stay on the menu.  Great vibe/ambiance. Cool rustic feel with exposed brick.  Amazing service and above average wine list.  Highly recommend this restaurant.
(Translated by Google) Nice place, with authentic dishes and reasonable prices.  (Original) Lugar bacana, com pratos autênticos e preços razoáveis.
Delish. Excellent food and service. I enjoyed every dish and appetizer I ordered. Only downside is that it is loud/noisy and difficult to have meaningful conversation.
Great food. Great Orange Wine
The chicken was good, the atmosphere was nice but nothing too special. The menu is limited and disappointing

Fantastic meal and great service. Came without a reservation, so originally we were waiting for a bar seat. However, the minute someone canceled over the phone we were seated as if we had a reservation. The cauliflower appetizer was delicious and flavorful. The salmon entrée was cooked perfectly and came with crunchy lentils and a  delicious tzatiki. The maple custard dessert was rich and creamy. Highly recommend the restaurant as long as you have a reservation.
Nice atmosphere.
Don't bother coming if you don't have a reservation.  Staff didn't bother to tell me that over the phone.

Service was very good and our water glasses were constantly filled. Pasta was cooked el dente, but too greasy and heavy to taste anything else but melted cheese. The halibut was probably the worst halibut I've had: way overcooked, didn't taste fresh, topped with an incompatible sweet sauce then placed on top of a boring big bed of sweet and sour beets. The short rib is plain and dry, served with similarly plain and bland black beans and cheese. Given the price and the difficulty to get a table here, the food quality is well below expectation and I am not to return. I don't get the hype of the place really.

Everything here is delicious, especially the pastas. While it's hard to get reservations, you can get a seat at a table or at the nice big bar when doors open, which is actually my favorite place to eat. The bartenders are really friendly and knowledgeable, and are happy to mix you custom cocktails while you eat.
Casual dining with amazing food and pasta.
Great Italian oriented restaurant, cozy feel and great food.
Always good. Great drinks, great food, and approachable servers. Always consistent. Get the pasta ragu

Had a marvelous birthday dinner at Marcel's! The food was wonderful and was only matched by the service. It was terrific to have such a yummy meal and wonderful service. The Dover sole was delicious, and the individual chocolate soufflé with crème anglaise was divine. There aren't enough superlatives to describe what a delightful evening it was. Would highly recommend this as a restaurant for a special occasion!

Our overall experience was perfection! To celebrate my 40th birthday dinner at Marcel's was one of the best meals we have ever had! From the moment we walked in until the moment we left, nothing could have been better! All the staff were consummate professsionals, the cocktails were extremely delicious and the food was extraordinary!
Really knowledgeable waiter helped us pick an amazing wine and helped us decide between a number of amazing sounding dishes. Everything we ordered was notable and especially​ delicious!
They valet cars on the street, so don't be over 2hrs you will get a "TICKET"

Loved the cozy atmosphere and everything we tried on the menu was delicious! Met the girls for a couple glasses of wine and shared a few dishes. It was hard to decide what to order because everything sounded so good. We shared sorbet and the maple custard at the end of the night. It tasted like heaven!
First time here for date night and the food was amazing. Had the spicy lamb sausage pasta. My wife had the rigatoni and it was incredible as well.
Great atmosphere, very good service, interesting cocktails, unique menu, very reasonable prices. The wine selection could be better.

Friendly, knowledgeable, attentive staff.  Ordered trout rillettes, grilled octopus, rigatoni, short ribs, and halibut.  Everything was very flavorful and delicious. Not too heavy on the sauces.  The octopus was nicely done, tender and not too charred.  Halibut was moist and matched well with the saffron sauce.  The trout rillettes paired really well with the frisee.  Dessert was the brownie and custard. Both very delicious. The custard was a bit too sweet for my palate but the hazelnut crust was a nice touch for texture.
So so delicious. Nicest staff too

Food is good, waiters are attentive, cocktails fantastic. Small, but we'll curated wine list. Every appetizer and pasta dish was perfectly prepped and cooked. Our group literally tried every dish on the menu and we were blown away by right proportions of food and taste. It's a farm to table restaurant. Highly recommended.  Owners of this place just opened up a pizzeria nearby called All-Purpose pizza.
Good food, overpriced, terrible beer.
Everything was perfect!
Great food - my go-to spot in DC
Amazing, delicious. Wonderful service. Great desserts.
Fabulous food
The Rigatoni is their signature dish and is definitely worth trying.
Food was.good, small plates though
Outstanding. Amazing world class gourmet food.
Best restaurant in the Bloomingdale area right now.

Been there 2 times about 3 years apart and both times were outstanding. The service is always amazing with great recommendations for wine everytime. We still talk about the food and the ambiance is fitting for a farm to table restaurant. Anytime we are back in DC we will be sure to stop and eat here.
Phenomenal Italian food. Every pasta dish on the menu seems better than the last.

Great neighborhood spot with seasonal rustic Italian inspired food.  It was Saturday night so we had to stalk a spot at the bar but worth the wait.  I recommend booking a reservation if you can.  Everything we had from apps to dessert was awesome.
Great place to eat
Great service. Chill atmosphere. Amazing for food.
Really great dining space and the fresh pasta is absolutely wonderful.

Food is superb: beer salad is light, fresh, and unique, brussels sprouts are addictively tasty and crispy, spaghetti squash is perfection, roasted chicken is juicy and flavorful, and their spin on creme brûlée is rich, creamy, and nutty. Don't miss anything with corn or burrata in the summer. Don't miss the off-menu caccio e pepe pasta. Service is solicitous. The space feels smaller than it is due to the close tables and its perennially booked to capacity nature, though it is warm and comfortable. Be warned — the bill adds up very quick. One of our favorites.
Delicious food and fantastic drinks. This is truly one of the new DC gems. Can get very busy, so be prepared to wait for a table or a spot at the bar.
Book a month in advance and don't expect to get a decent time. Very expensive food but well worth it.
Fantastic space and food! Scallops are a must!

This is the best restaurant in Bloomingdale!  We have a friend who every time she comes to DC for work, we get together at the Red Hen and for the three of us order the five or six pastas they have on the menu currently.  Everything is always tremendous we have never not loved all the pastas.  Make sure to make a reservation, but if you forgot you can generally get seats for two at the bar with out much of a wait and can still order the whole menu.
(Translated by Google) Very good  (Original) Muy bueno
Could not seat 2 people.....

Ate at the bar last night. Food was terrific, came quickly (despite the crowd) and the service was genial and accommodating. Chicken liver mousse, rigatoni with fennel sausage, and beef short rib were all top notch.
We have been here several times and always have great food, not even an exaggeration. The pate is amazing,don't miss it.

Our dinner at the Red Hen was great in many ways. The dishes were all very good -- pasta with pea shoot crema was delicious. So was the cauliflower. For me, the other dishes looked and tasted great; they just were not quite as special as they should be considering the price point. Service was overly attentive with server and other wait staff making too frequent laps in the dining room.
Make a reservation.  Highly recommend the swordfish!
Awesome

Finally came this way. The place has a great decor and feels perfect for this starting fall weather. We waited by the bar for approximately 45 minutes prior to be seated at a table. While waiting we had som delicious cocktails. Once seated we tried the delicious food. We had two of the small plates, two appetizers and then one pasta and one main dish. We had the ricotta crostini, chicken liver, burrata with grilled zucchini and the charred octopus. All of these plates were deliciously well prepared. Hard to find a favorite one. Then we had the mezze rigatoni and the porchetta. While both were great, the rigatoni won by a good advantage. The porchetta could have been a bit crispier, and less cooked inside as it was a bit tough. This said, was one of the best porchetta and definitely better than if I had cooked. A place to try again.
You will have a delicious meal every single time you come here. Go pasta to keep the cost down on your overall tab.
Everything was incredible.
Great Italian food and wine in a cozy restaurant. The brick matched well with the wood accents and the service was great
Worth it. Really great service and the food was delicious. I recommend the brussels sprouts, the scallops, and the ricotta pasta.
Have the rigatoni!
A great DC gem, the Red Hen serves food that is prepared with care and a talented hand. Everywhere you sit is a cozy place including the bar. I will be back soon.
I can't express how amazing our experience was here.  Every bit of the food and wine AND dessert was well worth the price!
One of the best restaurants in DC, hands down.

A space that's made to feel larger than it actually is. Red Hen offers locally sourced fare that is completely delicious. One of the better dining experiences I've had in a while with regards to the customer service. My party was waiting a little longer than expected because of how busy the restaurant was and without any prompting our server offered us free desert! Elegant and modern but with a rustic feel. The food is reasonably priced for it's quality and the deserts are to die for. I had an interesting cultural realization while I was dining however. I and the rest of my party, were the only African-American's in the restaurant other than members of the service staff. This was particularly strange because of the historically African-American neighborhood that the restaurant is in. The space definitely gives an intense feeling of how the neighborhood space is gentrifying and the juxtaposition of the clientele with the neighborhood right outside of it's window, was an experience that I was completely unable to ignore.
Red hen is one of those places where no matter what's on the menu you know it's gonna the best. Great beer and wine selection, amazing service staff, and again the best food.
My number-one go-to when introducing friends and family to DC. The atmosphere is great, the food is fantastic, and the seasonal menu is always exciting. Do yourself a favor and plan for the dessert.
Wow. Best pasta I have had in DC. Get the Rigatoni with Fennel Sausage or the Cavatelli. Also in terms of wines you must try the Multipuciano.

Not sure what the hype is all about.  The food was fine but nothing special or memorable.  Waitress recommended the octopus which was rubbery and served over a salty base of beans that could have come from a can frankly. Very expensive for the value received.  Menu very limited and the wood fired oven in limited evidence across all categories.  When friends say "Oh you have to try this" you know it is a hit.  No such sharing went on last evening. I'd give it a miss.

I had really high expectations for red hen. The food was good. Some of the food (pastas, in particular) were great. They have an interesting wine list with servers who know what they are serving. Maple custard dessert was awesome. But I found the service to be pushy (they were clearly trying to turn our table), the prices high, and the general experience not what I was hoping for. I would like to try it again.

This was some of the best food of my life. There is a long wait, but it's definitely worth it. The servers were very knowledgeable and had good recommendations. The zucca pasta and the chicken were incredible. Finish off your meal with the maple custard!

Food is good here, but I really like the rustic ambiance, open kitchen and overall space here.  The wait for a table is long and the acoustics are such that it's very loud. I'll definitely be back to try more dishes.

What a great space and great food. An awesome addition to the city and a great "destination" trip to Bloomingdale to break up the monotony of the usual 14th Street/Chinatown/Dupont/Georgetown scenes in town.

I recently  (5/3/2014) ate here for the second time and as  the first time, the food here is delicious. We arrived at 5 pm when they opened because we couldn't get a reservation at a decent time so we ate at the bar. We were greeted within minutes and served our drinks promptly. Having been here before, I knew I wanted the Burrata (a creamy, firm cheese dish similar to mozzarella). We also started with the smoked salmon with the creamy horseradish. To say delicious would be an understatement. We followed up with the rockfish with creamy polenta and the wood grilled chicken with kale and potatoes. Needless to say, I left full but not overly stuffed and happy with the service. The only reason I didn't give it 5 stars is because this place is relatively small, so we couldn't get a reservation until 9:30 pm which is too late for me. Although eating at the bar was fine, towards the end we had hoverers (people that stand behind you and make you want to hurry up and pay your bill so they can have your seat). Otherwise, I had a great time.

I had been wanting to try Red Hen and am so glad I did. I had carry out (technically delivery from a 3rd party service) from Red Hen, so I can not speak to the service or experience there. The Smoked Ricotta Crostini was a crostini with flavored butter with a delicious flavor. The Burrata was delicious as well with various flavors. The Baked Semolina Gnocchi was also lovely though I would have preferred if they used something other than mushrooms but it was still good. For dessert, the Maple Custard was fantastic! I hope to get the chance to dine on-site sometime soon.

Recommended by a barista about 10 minutes west on Florida. Took a chance, scored a table for 2 when a reservation didn't show. Wanted an appasimento or ripasso, didn't recognize anything on the menu. Server said "You should talk to Sebastian". Sebastian, one of the owners, recommended Negroamora, "at $45, a steal". HE WAS SO RIGHT. Wife wanted to split a salad, no problem switching the dressing, salad was awesome. Her pasta: Rabbit sugo with vegetables. Mine: Rigatoni with anis and sausage. Both plates well sized (neither nouvelle cuisine small nor American diner huge). I love rich food, I barely finished mine. Dessert. Well. Torn, I took the first one, figured I'd be linear and take the second next time. Toasted almond and bitter chocolate tart with homemade mint ice cream. Absolutely incredible flavour pairings. Service: Excellent. Atmosphere: Excellent. Food: Excellent. Wine: Excellent. All in, $110, not bad at all for what we had.
Nice place but a bit loud for dinner
Amazing food, great service, awesome atmosphere. Had grilled octopus for an app, it was so good! Highly recommend.
